reviews.review:
Buy [b]Left 4 Dead 2[/b] instead of this. The [b]second[/b] game features... 

- Every single bit of content from the first game; 
- A more stable version of the engine for modern systems and Linux; 
- Toggle to play in L4D1 mode (with guns and zombies from the first game only); 
- Steam Workshop support, where you can get the user interface, developer commentary and viewmodels from the first game;
- Community fixes for all L4D1 content that Valve left broken;
- A more active community, with full servers all the time.

Also, Turtle Rock Studios gets more credit for the development of this game than they deserve. Back 4 Blood is looking rough right now, and they are not transparent about how many developers from L4D are still working at the company.
